Tableau Workbench
=================

The current build requires:

- OCaml 4.12.x
- Findlib
- ExtLib
- Camlp5 7.14

Recommended OPAM setup
======================

Create the build switch and install the dependencies:

    opam switch create tableau-workbench ocaml-base-compiler.4.12.1
    opam install --switch=tableau-workbench ocamlfind extlib camlp5.7.14

Configure and build TWB:

    opam exec --switch=tableau-workbench -- ./configure
    make

The generated Makefile records the selected OPAM toolchain, so subsequent
`make` commands do not depend on which switch is active in the current shell.

Build and test the bundled provers
==================================

Build the propositional and modal logic provers:

    make provers

For example, run the propositional prover with:

    printf 'p v ~ p\n' | ./library/pc.twb

The generated prover executables are written to `library/`.

Installation
============

To install the compiler and library files:

    make install

Depending on the selected installation prefix, this may require appropriate
filesystem permissions.
